# League Client MCP

You are working with a **live League of Legends Client** via the `league-client-mcp` MCP server.
The server bridges tool calls to a Pengu Loader plugin inside the LoL Client over WebSocket.

## Architecture

```
Cursor Agent  ──MCP stdio──►  MCP Server (Node.js)
                                  │  ws://127.0.0.1:8080
                                  ▼
                       Pengu Loader Plugin  (inside LoL Client)
                                  │  DOM · CSS · JS · LCU fetch()
                                  ▼
                       League of Legends Client  (CEF / Ember.js)
```

League must be running with Pengu Loader active. 15 MCP tools available.

## Standard Workflow

```
1. get_lol_dom_snapshot   → map current page, find selectors
2. inject_lol_css         → prototype visual changes
3. query_lol_element      → verify selector or computed style
4. inject_lol_plugin      → add persistent JS + CSS behaviour
5. reload_lol_plugin      → iterate after code changes
6. export_plugin_to_pengu → write plugin to disk
7. reload_lol_client      → activate exported plugin permanently
```

## Tool Quick Reference

| Tool | When to use |
|---|---|
| `get_lol_dom_snapshot` | Start of every session — map the page |
| `query_lol_element` | Verify one selector without a full snapshot |
| `inject_lol_css` | CSS-only prototyping (replaces previous CSS) |
| `execute_lol_javascript` | One-off JS reads or quick checks |
| `inject_lol_plugin` | Persistent behaviour (JS + CSS, survives navigation) |
| `remove_lol_plugin` / `reload_lol_plugin` | Teardown or hot-reload a plugin |
| `export_plugin_to_pengu` | Make a plugin permanent on disk |
| `lcu_request` | Read/write LCU REST API (game data, summoner, lobby) |
| `click_lol_element` | Click a UI element |
| `type_into_lol_element` | Type into an input |
| `wait_for_lol_element` | Wait for element after navigation |
| `get_lol_client_state` | Current URL and active plugin names |
| `get_lol_performance_metrics` | Heap, DOM nodes, paint timings |
| `reload_lol_client` | Full client reload |

## Key LCU Endpoints

### Summoner
- `GET /lol-summoner/v1/current-summoner` — id, puuid, displayName, summonerLevel
- `GET /lol-summoner/v2/summoners/puuid/{puuid}` — summoner by PUUID

### Gameflow
- `GET /lol-gameflow/v1/gameflow-phase` — `None`·`Lobby`·`ChampSelect`·`InProgress`·`EndOfGame` etc.
- `GET /lol-gameflow/v1/session` — full game session data

### Champion Select
- `GET /lol-champ-select/v1/session` — picks, bans, timer, phase
- `PATCH /lol-champ-select/v1/session/actions/{id}` — hover/lock champion
- `GET /lol-champ-select/v1/session/my-selection` — my champion and spells
- `GET /lol-champ-select/v1/pickable-champion-ids` — available picks

### Lobby
- `GET /lol-lobby/v2/lobby` — current lobby
- `POST /lol-lobby/v2/lobby` — create lobby `{queueId}`
- `POST /lol-lobby/v2/lobby/matchmaking/search` — start queue
- `GET /lol-lobby/v2/received-invitations` — pending invitations

### Chat
- `GET /lol-chat/v1/friends` — friends with availability
- `GET /lol-chat/v1/me` — my chat state
- `PUT /lol-chat/v1/me` — update status / availability
- `POST /lol-chat/v1/conversations/{id}/messages` — send message

### Ranked
- `GET /lol-ranked/v1/current-ranked-stats` — tier, LP, wins, losses
- `GET /lol-ranked/v1/ranked-stats/{puuid}` — any player's stats

### Match History
- `GET /lol-match-history/v1/products/lol/current-summoner/matches` — recent matches
- `GET /lol-match-history/v1/games/{gameId}` — full game data

### Mastery & Runes
- `GET /lol-champion-mastery/v1/local-player/champion-mastery` — all mastery
- `GET /lol-perks/v1/pages` — rune pages | `PUT /lol-perks/v1/currentpage` — set active

### Loot & Inventory
- `GET /lol-loot/v1/player-loot` — loot inventory
- `GET /lol-inventory/v1/wallet` — wallet balance (RP, BE)
- `GET /lol-champions/v1/inventories/{summonerId}/champions` — owned champions

### Honor & End of Game
- `GET /lol-honor-v2/v1/ballot` — post-game honor ballot
- `GET /lol-end-of-game/v1/eog-stats-block` — post-game stats

## Plugin Code Conventions

```js
// Always return a cleanup function
const obs = new MutationObserver(() => {
  clearTimeout(window._t);
  window._t = setTimeout(render, 350);
});
obs.observe(document.body, { childList: true, subtree: false });
const interval = setInterval(render, 5000);
render();
return () => { obs.disconnect(); clearInterval(interval); };
```

- Debounce MutationObserver ~350 ms for Ember.js async DOM updates
- Use `fetch('/lcu-endpoint')` inside plugins — no auth needed
- `DataStore.set('k', v)` / `DataStore.get('k')` for persistent storage
- Position overlays: `position: fixed; z-index: 99999; pointer-events: none`
- Always call `export_plugin_to_pengu` + `reload_lol_client` to persist a plugin

## CSS Conventions

- `!important` on every declaration (LoL CSS is heavily layered)
- Design tokens: `--font-display`, `--font-body`, `--color-gold-{1-5}`, `--color-blue-{1-6}`, `--color-grey-{1-6}`
- Common selectors: `.lol-navigation`, `.screen-root.active`, `.champion-select`, `.profile-wrapper`, `.chat-typeahead-input`

## Constraints

- CEF/Chromium: ES2020+ JS; no Node.js or browser extension APIs
- `inject_lol_css` replaces entire stylesheet on each call
- Injected plugins cleared on client reload — `export_plugin_to_pengu` makes them permanent
- 15 s WebSocket timeout if LoL Client or Pengu Loader is not running
